messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
The baby's not breathing.
What's the location?
1280 Highland Avenue.
1280 Highland? Is this a house or an apartment?
It's a house.
Okay, what's the phone number that you're calling from?
It's [phone number].
Now, ma'am, stay on the line with me. I'm going to connect you over to fire rescue, okay?
Okay.
This is C-17 connecting 1280 Highland Avenue. Information verified.
What is the problem? Tell me exactly what happened.
Hello? Can you talk to me?
Okay. Calm down so we can help the baby, okay?
Okay.
I need to ask you some questions. Is the baby male or female?
Male.
Is the baby conscious?
No.
Is the baby breathing?
No, he's not breathing. Please help.
Okay. I've got help on the way. We're going to help the baby, okay? Did you see what happened?
I was sleeping. I went to check, and he was not breathing.
Are you with the baby right now?
I'm outside.
I need you to be by the baby. Can you get to the baby?
She's got him in her arms.
I need the baby to be laying flat on his back on the ground. Remove any pillows. Is there anything in the baby's mouth?
No.
Okay. Place your hand on the baby's forehead, the other hand under the baby's neck and shoulders. Then slightly tilt the head back. Can you feel or hear any breathing?
No.
Alright, listen to me. Do not stop what we are doing. Can you feel any breathing?
No, we can't.
Okay, I'm going to tell you how to give mouth-to-mouth. When the baby's head is slightly tilted back, completely cover the baby's mouth and nose with yours and blow two puffs of air into the lungs.
Okay, I'll do it.
Just enough to make the chest rise with each breath. Did you feel the air going in and out?
I'm not sure. He's got fluid in his lungs.
You still need to blow air into the lungs. What is your name?
My name is Nelson. My son's turning white.
Is someone doing chest compressions?
Yes, she's doing them.
Make sure to use two fingers on the breastbone in the center of his chest, right between the nipples. Push down hard and fast.
There's a fire station right down the street. What is going on?
They're on their way, sir. We need to keep working on the baby. Is she continuing CPR?
Yes, but he's turning purple.
Okay, keep going. They're almost there. I see the lights.
I see the lights. Please hurry up!
